# AI Chatbot Page — Full-Page LLM Chat with Coral Result Context

Add a dedicated, full-page **AI Chatbot** screen to the Coral Mobile app. The chatbot communicates with the local Qwen 2.5 LLM (via the Flask backend's `/api/chat` endpoint) and can automatically read and explain coral analysis results.

## Current State

The app currently has a **bottom-sheet mini-chat** (`_ReefGuideDrawer`) inside [result_page.dart](file:///c:/Users/luqma/OneDrive/Desktop/CHI/BASEPROJECT/09_MobileApps/Coral%20Mobile%20-%20Codex/lib/src/features/assessment/pages/result_page.dart#L201-L457) that opens when the user taps "Ask" on the result page. This mini-chat:
- Uses **hardcoded suggestion-chip responses** (not the LLM).
- Has a **read-only text input** — the user cannot type freely.
- Does **not** call the backend `/api/chat` API at all.

## What Will Change

| Aspect | Before | After |
|---|---|---|
| Chat location | Bottom-sheet overlay on result page | Full dedicated page + bottom nav tab |
| LLM integration | None (hardcoded responses) | Real HTTP calls to Flask `/api/chat` → Qwen 2.5 |
| User input | Tap suggestion chips only | Free-text input + suggestion chips |
| Prediction context | Not passed to backend | Automatically passed as `predictionContext` |
| Navigation | Only reachable via "Ask" button | Bottom nav tab **+** "Ask" button on result page |

